ğŸ• Pizza Ordering
A beginner-friendly Python script that simulates a pizza ordering system.
It calculates the final bill based on the size of the pizza and selected extras like pepperoni and cheese.

ğŸ’¡ Features
1.You can choose your pizza size: Small (S), Medium (M), or Large (L)
2.Add-ons:
   a)Pepperoni
   b)Extra cheese
3.Calculates the final price based on your choices

ğŸ’° Pricing Rules
1.Pizza Sizes:
  a)Small: $15
  b)Medium: $20
  c)Large: $25
2.Pepperoni:
  a)+$2 for Small
  b)+$3 for Medium or Large
  c)Extra Cheese: +$1 (any size)
